==English==
===Noun===
'''gynocentrism'''
#An ideological focus on females, and issues affecting them, possibly to the detriment of non-females.  Contrast with [[androcentrism]].

===Related Terms===
'''gynocentric''' (adj.):  Ideologically focused on females, and issues affecting them, possibly to the detriment of males.  Contrast with [[androcentric]].